title: [Caffe2] ONNX prepare error
body_html:
I am getting an error when running: caffe2.python.onnx.backend.prepare(model)

The error is:
Traceback (most recent call last):
File "test.py", line 20, in
prepared_backend = caffe2.python.onnx.backend.prepare(model)
File "/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/caffe2/python/onnx/backend.py", line 776, in prepare
pred_model = cls.optimize_onnx(model, predict=True)
File "/anaconda2/lib/python2.7/site-packages/caffe2/python/onnx/backend.py", line 733, in optimize_onnx
out = onnx.optimizer.optimize(input, passes)
TypeError: optimize(): incompatible function arguments. The following argument types are supported:
1. (arg0: str, arg1: List[unicode]) -> str

The ONNX file has been exported from PyTorch. Strangely it works fine if using onnx-caffe2 repo.
I have tried both the Conda version of Caffe2 and building from source.
Python 2.7

My onnx file: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1L8pVfZ6ZEExvtG5aZTPpbo_st7opNQZT/view?usp=sharing
